    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "EVERETT, April 5.-Right-of-\nway negotiations Just completed\nmake this city the terminus of the\nMilwaukee road on the coast. The\nfairgrounds will be used for freight\ngrounds and the line will reach the\nwaterfront by a tunnel. A union\ndepot for use of the Milwaukee,\nSouthern Pacific and Canadian Pa\ncific, in the center of town, is\nplanned. J. ID. Farrell acting for\nthe Hartman interests, concluded\nthe deal. A joint use of rackage\nis included."
    }
  ]
